data.text:
Rob Paulsen (born March 11, 1956) is an American voice actor, singer and former movie and television actor. He was starred as the cast member for Saturday Night Live (1981-1982) and he has done many voice roles in various movies, television programs and video games. He is best known for his roles as Brain from Pinky and the Brain, P.J. in A Goofy Movie and Goof Troop, Carl Sneezer from The Adventures of Jimmy Neutron Boy Genius, Raphael (1987) and Donatello (2012) from Teenage Mutant Ninja Turtles and Yakko Warner and Dr. Otto Scratchansniff from Animaniacs.
